Package gitlet

Class Commit

java.lang.Object
gitlet.Commit
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Commit extends Object implements Serializable
This class represents a Commit, which contains information about a certain commit, including its message, timestamp, parent(s), and of course, its Blobs.

  • Method Details

    • getHash

      public String getHash()
      Returns the SHA-1 hash of the given commit.

    • importCommit

      public static Commit importCommit(String commitHash)
      Returns a Commit, pulled from the inputted COMMITHASH, which is the filename of this Commit within the Commits folder.

    • exportCommit

      public void exportCommit()
      Writes the current commit to its corresponding file in the Commits folder. Updates its contents if it already exists, creates new file if it does not yet exist.

    • validCommit

      public boolean validCommit()
      Returns whether the current Commit is a valid Commit. Validity is ensured by checking that either the Add Stage or the Remove Stage is not empty.

    • processStage

      public void processStage()
      Processes the Add and Remove Stages of this Commit, first importing all Blobs from its parent Commit, then adding all items from this Commit's Add Stage, then removing all items from this Commit's Remove Stage.

    • contains

      public boolean contains(Blob blob)
      Returns whether this Commit contains BLOB.

    • hasAnyParent

      public boolean hasAnyParent()
      Returns whether this Commit has a parent Commit. Equivalent to checking whether this Commit is the initial Commit, as that should be the only Commit without a parent.

    • hasParent1

      public boolean hasParent1()
      Returns whether this commit has first parent.

    • hasParent2

      public boolean hasParent2()
      Returns whether this commit has second parent.

    • findModifiedFiles

      public static Map<String,String> findModifiedFiles(Commit commit)
      Given the Commit, COMMIT, returns a TreeMap of all files within this Commit that are modified or deleted, but not staged. The TreeMap maps a filename to its status, either "(modified)" or "(deleted)".

    • findUntrackedFiles

      public static List<String> findUntrackedFiles(Commit commit)
      Returns an ArrayList of files that exist in the Current Working Directory, but do not exist in the given COMMIT or any of the Stages.

    • getFilesMap

      public Map<String,String> getFilesMap()
      Returns a TreeMap of the current Commit's commitMap, minus any of the magic keys.

    • equals

      public boolean equals(Commit other)
      Returns whether this Commit is equal to OTHER.

    • fileExistsInCommit

      public static boolean fileExistsInCommit(String fileName, Commit commit)
      Returns whether FILENAME exists in COMMIT.

    • fileModified

      public static boolean fileModified(String fileName, Commit other, Commit commit)
      Returns whether the file, FILENAME, is unchanged between two Commits, OTHER and COMMIT. Make sure that the file exists in both Commits first. Returns true if file is modified, returns false if file is the same in both Commits.
